 They are sending a car for me in a few minutes.'

'I see. Do you think —'

'You will be at the hospital as early as possible, won't you? — at nine, at eight, even earlier...'

'Yes, of course.'

'I told the maid — and perhaps you will look into the matter too when I am gone — I told her —'

Krug heaved horribly, could not finish — crushed down the receiver. His study was unusually cold. All of them so blind and sooty, and hung up so high above the bookshelves, that he could hardly m